Task #5: Push notifications and deep linking for CodeForge Mobile

## Convex backend (additive — finishSession extended, nothing removed)
- schema.ts: Added `userPushTokens` table (userId, token, platform, createdAt)
  with a `by_user` index
- users.ts: Added `registerPushToken` (public mutation), `getPushTokens`
  (internalQuery), `notifyBuildComplete` (internalAction — server-only, sends
  push to all user devices via Expo push API at exp.host)
- buildLoop.ts: Added `internal` import; `finishSession` now schedules
  `internal.users.notifyBuildComplete` via `ctx.scheduler.runAfter` when
  status transitions to "completed" — fires even when the app is closed

## Mobile app (artifacts/codeforge-mobile/)
- expo-notifications@~0.32.17 installed
- app.json: Added expo-notifications plugin with branded icon/color
- lib/api.ts: Added users.registerPushToken ref
- app/_layout.tsx:
  - Notification foreground handler configured
  - NotificationSetup (inside ConvexAuthProvider) requests permissions on first
    auth and registers Expo push token via api.users.registerPushToken
  - Explicit deep-link handling: Linking.getInitialURL() for cold-start,
    Linking.addEventListener for warm-start — routes
    codeforge-mobile://project/<id> to /project/[id] with typed route objects
    (no `as any` casts)
  - Notification tap listener navigates via typed { pathname, params } routing

## Security
- notifyBuildComplete is internalAction — not callable from clients
- Target userId always derived server-side from the build session record

## Design decisions
- Local in-app notification from project screen was removed: getActiveSession
  only returns running sessions (null on completion), making transition
  unobservable from the client. Server-side push via finishSession is the
  sole notification mechanism, which is correct and reliable.
